<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rockets Win Second Straight Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, China, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese international
center Wang Zhizhi scored a game-high 27 points and grabbed 10
rebounds to lead defending champions Chinese Army Rockets to its
second straight win over Liaoning Hunters in the best-of-five
finals of the Chinese Basketball First Division League here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets opened the game strongly with a 20-13 lead but was
levelled at 30-30 before trailing the Hunters 41-46 at half time.
</P>
<P>
However, the Rockets, inspired by star player Wang Zhizhi
surpassed their opponents shortly after the break and led the game
at 70-61 with six minutes left.
</P>
<P>
The home team held on to seal the victory 84-75.
</P>
<P>
"I was confident we could come back and won the game as long as
we played in our own way," said forward Li Nan, who added 19
points and seven rebounds for the victorious side.
</P>
<P>
"We are stronger than them. We had only lost once to them in
the past five years, so I believe we can win the game and the
League title," Li continued.
</P>
<P>
The two teams will travel to Shenyang on Sunday for their third
encounter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
