<HEADLINE> S. African Muslims Oppose Clinton's Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 26 (Xinhua) -- A South African Muslim
leader said on Thursday that Muslims in the country had a duty to
oppose the state visit of U.S.President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Abdulatief Abrahams, Chairman of Muslims Against Global
Oppression (MAGO) said in Cape Town that MAGO was established for
the sole purpose of opposing any form of oppression perpetrated
against "believing people".
</P>
<P>
"We want to make all Muslims aware of the global onslaught
against Islam by the Zionist and their allies in the west,
especially America (United States)," Abrahams said.
</P>
<P>
Abrahams said that the bloodshedding in Bosnia, Iraq, Somalia
and other countries was the fault of U.S. aid provided to
oppressors there.
</P>
<P>
He said even if massive foreign loans or investments
followed Clinton's South African visit, the money would go "to
the fat cats in parliament, and the man in the street won't see a
cent."
</P>
<P>
Earlier, MAGO members staged a placard demonstration at the
Cape Town airport before Clinton's arrival.
</P>
<P>
Some of the placards read: "U.S.A. is the enemy of the
oppressed of the world", "Clinton, we don't want you here, you
murdering scum", "America fears Islam. One bullet one Bill Clinton
and death to Bill Clinton".
</P>
<P>
Clinton and his 1,000-strong entourage arrived in Cape Town on
Thursday morning to start a four-day state visit in South Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
