<HEADLINE> Twenty-two Kenyan Girls Die in School fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan police spokesman Peter
Kimanthi Thursday confirmed that 22 girls of Bombolulu Girls
Secondary School in the port city of Mombasa died in a mysterious
fire on Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that among those who were admitted to hospital,
five were in critical conditions while some 23 girl students were
treated and discharged.
</P>
<P>
According to the school headmistress Mersilla Mwasi, the
dormitory which had 144 students by the time it caught fire was
completely razed to the ground in the fierce blaze, the Kenya
News Agency (KNA) reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Coast Provincial Commissioner Timothy Sirma who visited
the school said that the government would make immediate
investigations to ascertain the cause of the fire.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi has sent a message of
condolence to the parents and relatives of the 22 victims and
instructed Kenyan police to investigate thoroughly the cause of
the fire.  
</P>
