<HEADLINE> Ethiopia: Planes Spraying Pesticide to Wipe Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Planes have been employed to
spray pesticide to mop out locusts in Ethiopia's Somali National
Region, the Somali Regional Agricultural Bureau (SRAB) said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted the bureau as saying that the
spraying has been conducted in Dembel and Feisa areas and the
work will continue in the locust-infested areas.
</P>
<P>
It was reported Monday that swarms of locust were seen
infesting Haroresa area in the northern part of Ethiopia's Somali
region, covering an area of 1,500 hectares.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia reported the situation to the Desert Locust Control
Organization for East Africa the same day.
</P>
<P>
According to SRAB, a surveillance has identified swarms of
locusts flying to the region from Red Sea and northern Somalia.
</P>
