<HEADLINE> Bus Accident Injures 18 in Dar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Two mini-buses collided
with each other Thursday in the Tanzanian capital of Dar es
Salaam, injuring 18 passengers.
</P>
<P>
Regional police commander Alfred Gewe confirmed the accident
and said the police are still investigating its cause.
</P>
<P>
The victims were sent to the city's largest hospital Muhimbili
Medical Center (MMC). Two people who suffered multiple injuries
have been admitted while the rest were treated and discharged.
</P>
<P>
MMC's Public Relations Officer McDonald Mwaijande said the two
who sustained multiple fractures are Eliabu Matemba, 36, and
Rajabu Mahanyu, 41, both residents of the Tabora Region in west
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Mahanyu said at the hospital bed that the accident happened
after one of the mini-buses was trying to divert from another car
which stopped suddenly in the front.
</P>
<P>
The victim said that some people attempted to make fortunes
from the mishap and ran toward the deformed mini-buses to loot
passengers' belongings. But they were stopped by nearby police
officers who came up to maintain the security order. 
</P>
