<HEADLINE> Nigerian Women Marry Young: Statistics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- More than 35 percent of Nigerian
women married before the age of 15, the Federal Office of
Statistics (FOS) have indicated.
</P>
<P>
Jigawa state in the north has the highest figure of 91
percent, with Niger state in the west records the lowest of 17
percent, FOS said, quoted by the News Agency of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
In its publication titled "Major Social Indicators 1993/94",
FOS said 67 percent of Nigerian households are without
electricity, with the highest at more than 90 percent in eight
states in the northern part and the lowest at three percent in
Lagos, the economic center.
</P>
<P>
The document also revealed that only 49 percent of adults in
the country are literate.
</P>
<P>
It said 31 percent of households in the country source their
water supply from streams, ponds or other unsatisfactory places.
</P>
<P>
While 87 percent or nine-tenths of Nigerians dispose of their
refuse in unsatisfactory places such as within their compounds or
other unauthorized areas, 33 percent of them use pail, bush,
streams and rivers or any other type of unconventional toilets
stand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
