<HEADLINE> 56 Countries Sign Contracts on World Horticulturial Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Fiftysix countries and two
international organizations today signed exhibition contracts with
China, the host of the World Horticulturial Expo scheduled for May,
1999.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from giant flower producers of France, Israel,
Japan, the Netherlands, Thailand and some other countries, as well
as from the Association of International Producers of Horticultures
(AIPH) and the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) signed
the contracts with the expo organizers of China.
</P>
<P>
Austria has decided to bring to the show a statue of great
musician Strauss together with its flower exhibits. And some other
countries have detailed their plans for the expo, the largest one
China has ever hosted.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day meeting in Kunming, capital of southwest
China's Yunnan Province, about 110 representatives visited the
construction site of the would-be exhibition hall.
</P>
<P>
They said they were impressed by the good job done by the
Chinese organizers.  
</P>
