<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Expert Calls for Transparency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- A leading Bangladeshi economist on
Friday called for transparency and accountability in planning and
carrying out development activities.
</P>
<P>
"In an aid-dependent country, unless donors design their aid
package according to the plans and programs of the aid-recipient
country, planning becomes a meaningless exercise," Professor
Mosharaff Hossain told the inaugural session of an international
workshop on planning, monitoring and evaluation, which opened here
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
He said that if the amount of over 30 billion U.S. dollars
Bangladesh received during the last two and a half decades had
been properly used, the levels of poverty, malnutrition and
unemployment in the country would have been much lower than what
is the case today.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Christian Commission for Development in
Bangladesh, the seven-day workshop was attended by 35 participants
from 14 countries, including the Netherlands and Peru. 
</P>
</TEXT>
