<HEADLINE> FIA Puts Temporary Brake on Three Teams </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- McLaren, Williams and Jordan
will be unable to use their innovative braking systems during
Friday's free trials while the motorsport's ruling body FIA
examines protests from Ferrari and other teams.
</P>
<P>
Ferrari claim the rear-wheel braking system, which played an
important role in the crushing domination of the opening round in
Australia by McLaren, is illegal.
</P>
<P>
Ferrari have been joined by Minardi, Sauber, Tyrrell and Arrows
in the protest, believing the system effectively creates
four-wheel driving, which is outlawed in Formula One. 
