<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Down Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE)-100 Index dropped 4.14 points Friday to close at 1564.48.
</P>
<P>
A total of 53 million shares were traded Friday against 66
million shares Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say the KSE-100 index went down slightly Friday amidst
profit taking by both local and institutional buyers ahead of the
weekend close.
</P>
<P>
Selling pressure was seen mainly on Pakistan Telecom Company
Limited, the bourse's volume leader, which drove the market down,
they say.
</P>
<P>
"The index is now at its lowest level in a fairly long while.
Next week is likely to bring fresh buying which will take the
index up," said Aqeel Karim Dhedhi, a broker at the KSE.
</P>
<P>
Volumes are also expected to improve as next week will be the
last full trade week prior to the Eid-ul-Azha religious holiday,
he said. 
</P>
