<HEADLINE> Association of Banks Decide to Lower Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The Committee of the Hong Kong
Association of Banks has decided to decrease the interest rates by
0.25 percent across the board, which will take effect on March 30
this year.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at the committee meeting here Friday.
After the readjustment, the interest rates both for savings and 24
Hours' Call/Notice may be paid on Hong Kong dollar deposits to the
respective maxima of 5.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
Major banks in Hong Kong including the Hong Kong and Shanghai
Bank, the Standard Chartered Bank and the Bank of China Hong Kong
Branch have all followed the decision.
</P>
<P>
When asked to comment the bank interest rate cut, Financial
Secretary Donald Tsang Yam-kuen said: "it could be welcome,
indicating they are now more confident about the market situation.
They had a rather rough hatch at the end of last year. It seems
that they believe that the market is now stabilizing and this is
welcome." 
</P>
</TEXT>
