<DOCNO> XIE19980327.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blatter Declares to Bid for President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- FIFA General-Secretary Sepp
Blatter Friday formally declared he will run for the presidency of
the world soccer ruling boday in Zurich.
</P>
<P>
Blatter handed his official notification to the outgoing FIFA
President Joao Havelang. In the statement, Blatter also asked
``for dispensation from certain duties so as to avoid any possible
conflict of interest''.
</P>
<P>
Blatter's rival for the presidency, UEFA President Johansson,
and his supporters have long argued that if Blatter is a
candidate, he should step down as FIFA's top manager immediately.
</P>
<P>
The deadline for Havelange to leave his post has been set on
April 7, and the election will take place at the FIFA Congress in
Paris on June 8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
