<HEADLINE> China Supports DPRK Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan said today that China supports the reasonable initiatives
and suggestions of the Workers Party of Korea and the government
of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) to ease the
sitution on the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
China fully supports the efforts made by the two sides on the
peninsula to gradually increase mutual trust, improve relations
through dialog and consultations, and eventually realize national
reunification on a self-reliant and peaceful basis, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks during a meeting with a visiting DPRK
delegation led by Vice-Foreign Minister Chon Jae Hong.
</P>
<P>
Tang said the Communist Party of China and the Chinese
government have consistently attached great importance to its
traditional friendly ties with the DPRK. He added that the new
government of China will continue to implement this policy.
</P>
<P>
The international situation is undergoing great and profound
changes, and the strengthening of Sino-Korean friendly relations
will not only be in the fundamental interests of the two nations
and the two peoples, but also be conducive to peace and stability
in Northeast Asia, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
"China is willing to continue its sincere efforts to help
achieve this end," said Tang.
</P>
<P>
Chon Jae Hong, who is visiting China for the first time, is
here as guest of the Foreign Ministry. He said the friendship
forged by the older generation of leaders of both countries has
taken roots amongst the people of the two nations.
</P>
<P>
He said Kim Jong Il has extended great effort to promote the
development of friendly ties with China. He expressed confidence
that joint efforts will ensure the relationship continues to grow
on the basis of "mutual support and cooperation".
</P>
<P>
Chon briefed Tang on the domestic situation in his country, and
noted that severe natural disasters in recent years have created
difficulties for his country's economic development and hardships
for the Korean people.
</P>
<P>
"The people of the DPRK are fully confident with their future
under the leadership of Comrade Kim Jong Il," said Chon.
</P>
<P>
He expressed sincere gratitude for China's assistance in
helping the DPRK overcome economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also exchanged views on other issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK delegation arrived in Beijing this morning.  
</P>
</TEXT>
