<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Parliament Rejects Change of Citizenship Rules </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 27 (xinhua) -- The German Parliament has rejected a
bill urging looser control over granting German nationality.
</P>
<P>
The 662-seat German parliament voted against the bill by
388 to 317.
</P>
<P>
The bill, proposed by the main opposition Social Democrat
Party, would have made it easier for children born to immigrant
parents to acquire German nationality.
</P>
<P>
The liberalization of citizenship laws have long been debated
in Germany. The 85-year-old law bases nationality on German
ancestry and allows no dual citizenship for those with
foreign-born parents.
</P>
<P>
The issue of liberalizing the citizenship law can only be
discussed in parliament again after the general elections in
September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
