<HEADLINE> HKSAR Justice Secretary Visits Supreme People's Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Elsie Leung Oi-sie, secretary of
justice of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR),
visited the Supreme People's Court this afternoon and held talks
with Zhu Mingshan, the court's vice-president.
</P>
<P>
Zhu told Leung that increasing exchanges between the legal
sectors in inland areas and the HKSAR under the principle of "one
country, two systems" will greatly enhance mutual understanding
and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Since the return of Hong Kong to the motherland, the Basic Law
of the HKSAR has been carried out in a comprehensive way, said
Zhu, adding that smooth implementation of the Basic Law is an
important task of the legal sectors in inland areas and Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
He expressed confidence that both sides will work to ensure
the success of the implementation.
</P>
<P>
Leung briefed Zhu on the HKSAR Department of Justice, and noted
that discussions with various departments have enabled her to gain
a better understanding of the legal system in inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders exchanged views on judicial contacts and
legal training programs between inland areas and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Leung also held talks with leading officials from the Supreme
People's Procuratorate, the State Council's Hong Kong and Macao
Affairs Office, the Department of Justice, the Department of
Public Security and the Commission of Legislative Affairs under
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will return to Hong Kong on Saturday.  
</P>
