<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1430 GMT March 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA -- President of the World Economic Forum (WEF) Klaus
Schwab has said the integration of Africa into the global economy
was "one of the greatest challenges in the 21st century".
</P>
<P>
Schwab made the remarks in his preface to the Africa
Competitiveness Report 1998, published recently by the WEF in
collaboration with the Harvard Institute of International
Development, according to a WEF press release. (World Economic
Forum-Africa)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin voiced his support
for Sergei Kiriyenko to become Russia's new prime minister on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The government and the presidential office would also support
Kiriyenko at the head of a new cabinet, Yeltsin said on national
radio.After Yeltsin dismissed the government on March 23,
Kiriyenko was appointed acting prime mnister and nominated to take
the office on Friday.
</P>
<P>
As an independent politician, the 35-year-old Kiriyenko is
skillful in keeping contacts with different parties, said
Yeltsin. (Russia-Yeltsin-Kiriyenko)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- Romanian Prime Minister Victor Ciorbea has defied
mounting pressure within the government and declared that he will
not resign.
</P>
<P>
In a strongly-worded statement, Ciorbea said Thursday he was
acting for the "stability of the nation".
</P>
<P>
He had been recommended for the post by the coalition and
approved by the parliament and president, he added.
</P>
<P>
Those wanting him to resign would have to go through the legal
channels by staging a no-confidence vote of his government,
otherwise he would not tender his resignation, he
stressed. 
</P>
