<HEADLINE> Afghan Warlord Gives 48-Hour Ultimatum to Vacate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Afghan ethnic-Uzbek warlord
Rashid Dostum has served an ultimatum to the Shiite Hezb-e-Wahdat
faction to leave Mazar-e-Sharif, about 300 km north of Kabul,
within 48 hours.
</P>
<P>
Otherwise, a general attack would be launched against the
faction, a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Dostum, who once formed the dominant power
in control of Mazar-e-Sharif, headquarters of Afghan anti-Taliban
alliance, has been attempting to regain control of the city.
</P>
<P>
Mazar-e-Sharif, the only largest city outside the control of
the Islamic Taliban militia, was taken by the Shiite Hezb-e-Wahdat
late last year when it led a massive defense of the city from a
major Taliban assault in September, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Clashes between Dostum and the Shiite Hezb-e-Wahdat faction,
two major factions of the ant-Taliban alliance, have intensified
recently inside the city, the report said. 
</P>
