<HEADLINE> European Airbus Producers to Form Single Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The four major European Airbus
producers in France, Germany, Britain and Spain announced Friday
plans to form a new single company for producing the passenger
planes.
</P>
<P>
Aerospatiale, British Aerospace, Daimler-Benz Aerspace and CASA
announced that they had reached "an agreement of principle on the
objectives, scale and operational structure of a future unified
European company".
</P>
<P>
"The four partners of Airbus, as well as their respective
governments, have a strategic interest in the construction of a
strong aerospace industry," they said without providing further
details.
</P>
<P>
The heads of the four companies have reportedly submitted a
confidential report to European governments on a wholesale
restructuring of Europe's aerospace and military industrial complex.
</P>
<P>
The move came after French President Jacques Chirac, German
Chancellor Helmut Kohl and British Prime Minister Tony Blair last
December asked European aerospace enterprises to submit a
memorandum by March 31 with detailed proposals on building a
European civil and defense aerospace industry.
</P>
<P>
Some other European aerospace giants, such as the Dassault
Aviation and Lagardere defense electronics group of France, the
Finmeccanica of Italy and Saab aircraft-maker of Sweden, are also
included in the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
