young to lead a government, saying that ability and energy do not
depend on one's age.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said that he had never doubted the loyalty and fidelity
of former Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, and he had asked
Chernomyrdin to prepare for the 2000 presidential election.
</P>
<P>
"I believe Chernomyrdin can make more contributions to Russia,"
the president said. 
