<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan-Russia Strategic Partnership to Be Continued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALAM ATA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan has pledged to
continue improving relations with Russia during a forthcoming
visit by President Boris Yeltsin, despite the sacking of Russian
cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Kazakh Foreign Minister Kasymzhomart Tokaye said in an
interview with Kazakh newspaper Panorama published Friday that the
two countries were building a strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
