former Energy Minister Sergei Kiriyenko, 35, as Acting Prime
Minister.
</P>
<P>
Tokaye said the forthcoming state visit by President Yeltsin to
Kazakhstan will mark a turning point in relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Relations were strained amid disagreements over the division of
the Caspian Sea, Russian debt to Kazakhstan, and tariffs following the
disintergration of the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
But since January, the two nations have carried out a series of
negotiations, reaching agreements on their differences. 
