<HEADLINE> Overseas Investors Favor Fuzhou Tourism Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Thursday groundbreaking ceremonies
for a foreign-funded race track in the Fuzhou Economic Development
Zone, Fujian Province, has marked the growing interest of overseas
investors in the local tourism projects.
</P>
<P>
The "Junshan Race Track" and "Junshan Jockey Club" will be part
of the province's first horse racing complex, according to local
sources.
</P>
<P>
The zone also inked contracts for foreign investments in 10
additional tourism projects valued at close to 84 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Fuzhou zone, located at the Minjiang River estuary,
functions as a high-tech industrial park, bonded zone, investment
zone for Taiwan investors and a pilot area for agricultural
cooperation across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
The zone is home to 600-odd foreign-funded enterprises which
recorded a total 1997 industrial output value of 10 billion
yuan (1.2 billion US dollars). The said enterprises
exported products valued at over 500 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
"The zone's service industry has lagged behind and offers great
potential for extensive development of the tourism industry,"
according to Lei Chengcai, director of the zone's Administrative
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Mawei Port, located at the mouth of the river, is considered to
be the birthplace of the Chinese navy and the "cradle" for China's
shipbuilding industry. The development zone offers the nation's
shortest shipping route to Taiwan island.
</P>
<P>
"Tourists from Taiwan can reach Fuzhou in only a few hours by
boat, with substantially less time required for air travel," said
Lei.
</P>
<P>
Eastern Fujian Province is the native home of numerous people
living in Taiwan, and the zone has employed various influential
businessmen from the island to consult on approaches for
attracting overseas investment for local tourism projects.
</P>
<P>
The zone also attempts to attract investments in an
additional 35 tourism projects valued at 250 million US dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
