<DOCNO> XIE19980327.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IMF Accepts "Mexican Model" in Solving Debt Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary Fund
(IMF) has agreed to Indonesia's proposal to follow the "Mexican
pattern" in settling its private foreign debts.
</P>
<P>
IMF Director for Asia-Pacific Hubert Neiss said here Friday:
"We can accept the Mexican model with certain modifications in a
bid to settle the private sector foreign debts."
</P>
<P>
Neiss made the remarks before meeting the Indonesian team to
discuss how the private foreign debt problem will be settled.
</P>
<P>
Neiss, however, declined to give details.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican model means giving a grace period of three to four
years to the private sector to repay their debt and providing an
affordable exchange rate for the rupiah (national currency)
against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah has been under severe pressure since July last year,
plunging to its lowest level of 17,000 to the greenback in
January, compared to 2,450 rupiah in the pre-crisis period in
July. It is trading at about 8,300 per dollar now.
</P>
<P>
This has caused most indebted companies to become technical
bankrupt as their foreign debts surpass their equity.
</P>
<P>
At the end of December last year, Indonesia's foreign debt
totaled to 137.424 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Economic experts held that the private sector's foreign debt is
one of the major causes of the monetary crisis in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
An IMF team led by Neiss has been here since March 18 to
discuss economic reforms in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980327.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Court of Final Appeal Expected Within 1998: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 27 (Xinhua) -- A senior justice official of the
Macao Government said on Friday that the Court of Final Appeal
should be established within 1998 so that it can gain experience
before the handover of power.
</P>
<P>
Secretary of Justice Jorge Silveira Justice made these remarks
while attending a seminar on the localization of the legal system.
</P>
<P>
"(We) hope that the Court of Final Appeal would be established
within 1998 so that it can operate for one year to gain the
necessary experience before the handover of power," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that several laws regarding the establishment of the
court had been drafted.
</P>
<P>
The consultation and study on the laws should be finished as
quickly as possible at the Macao Legislative Assembly, the
Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group, among others, so that the
laws can be promulgated in mid-1998, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Basic Law stipulates that the power of final
adjudication of the Macao Special Administrative Region shall be
vested in the Court of Final Appeal of the Region.
</P>
<P>
Silveira said a building will be constructed to house the Court
of Final Appeal and intermediate courts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
