<HEADLINE> Nepal to Produce Film on Yeti </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The Araniko Academy of Nepal
announced on Friday that it has decided to shoot a unique feature
film on Yeti, a mysterious biped roaming freely on the Himalayas.
</P>
<P>
The work will begin in September and is expected to take about
two years, said Gulab Khetan, advisor to the academy, a
non-governmental organization in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
The director will be a Nepalese, but a Western country will
provide technological support, he said.
</P>
<P>
He refused to disclose the name of the country, saying that
some details remain to be decided.
</P>
<P>
Yeti has long been a subject of awesome expectations and highly
fanciful conjecture, but it is indeed not like the enigmatic Big
Foot supposed to be playing hide-and-seek with the local
inhabitants in North American wilds, the academy said in a press
release.
</P>
<P>
Yeti is a reality experienced by many observers and occasional
mountaineers, and the film will take into account its objective
reality by furnishing details from legends, hearsay, supposed
encounters and other relative sources, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
It said scenes for the film will be shot at different locations
in Nepal like Mustang, Dhaulagiri, Lantang, Manaslu, Nupche, Gauri
Shankar and Ganesh Himal.
</P>
<P>
Besides the film, VCDs will also be produced for the
international audience, the press release added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
