<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise Marginally on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices finished mixed on
the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index (STII) grew marginally by merely 2.29 points to close at
1,653.93 points on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market started out steady, but interest
diminished later through the day. They were surprised that
developments like Keppel Corporation's planned takeover of
shipyard Hitachi Zosen Ltd and Temasek Holdings exchangeable bond
issue did not result in more active trading.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 236.41 million units, valued
at 306.47 million Singapore dollars (about 191.54 million U.S.
dollars). Declines led advances by 183 to 167, while 261 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Sel Properties was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 24.89 million shares. It was followed by
Easyknit which had 11.39 million shares traded. Uniphoenix was
next with 9.66 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led the gainers of the day as it rose by 1.3
dollars to finish at 38 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sembawang
increased by 80 cents to end at 13.8 Singapore dollars. UOB
(United Overseas Bank) Foreign was up by 50 cents to close at 9.5
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Hitachi Zosen was the biggest loser as it
declined by 17 cents to end at 77 Singapore cents. Local car
distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C), Cosco Warrant, and Robinson
each fell by 15 cents to close at 7.45 Singapore dollars, 22.5
Singapore cents, and five Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
