<HEADLINE> Duma Is Likely to Approve Kiriyenko's Nomination, Shokhin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Russia's State Duma (the lower
house of parliament) is most likely to approve President Boris
Yelstin's nomination of Sergei Kiriyenko as the new prime minister,
Alexander Shokhin, leader of Our Home is Russia faction in the
Duma said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin named Kiriyenko as the prime minister
and asked the Duma to approve his nomination in the first debate
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Under the Russian constitution, the Duma may be dissolved if it
rejects the candidate three times. But Shokhin held that the Duma
will move on the razor's edge and approve the candidate only at
the third try.
</P>
<P>
He did not rule out the possibility that the left-wing
opposition will opt for early parliamentary elections and reject
the candidate three times.
</P>
<P>
Duma Speaker Gennady Seleznyov believes that Kiriyenko, as an
official candidate, should hold a series of meetings with the
lower house, not only faction leaders.
</P>
<P>
He notified that the Duma is likely to hold the first debate on
the candidacy on April 3. 
