<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Asks Duma to Accept PM Nomination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Friday nominated Sergei Kiriyenko as the prime minister and asked
the State Duma (the lower house of parliament) to accept the
nomination, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin told reporters after meeting with Kiriyenko that he
hoped the Duma would save time and accept the nomination, said the
report.
</P>
<P>
If nomination is not accepted after three presentations, then
the Duma will get dissolved, he said in a letter to Duma Speaker
Gennady Seleznyov.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin dismissed the whole government on Monday and appointed
Kiriyenko as acting prime minister on the same day.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that reforms in Russia are in need of vigors, new
plans, more supervision, and young government members.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the 12 tasks of the government, Yeltsin said they
would be continuously carried out in spite of the government
reshuffle, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
