<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed lower Friday in thin volume as
investors were cautious of the market's immediate direction.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the Composite Index eased 5.69 points to 727.62,
the Emas Index shed 1.23 points to 184.09, the Industrial Index
fell 7.40 points to 1,306.11 and the second board index was 0.81
of a point lower to 181.71.
</P>
<P>
Losers outpaced gainers by 437 to 179, while 160 counters were
unchanged and 141 others were untraded.
</P>
<P>
Friday's turnover rose to 184.423 million shares valued at
419.656 million ringgit (about 117.88 million U.S. dollars) from
151.206 million shares worth 406.668 million ringgit (about
114.232 million U.S. dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover improved to 165.092 million shares
valued at 369.932 million ringgit (about 103.913 million U.S.
dollars) from 136.919 million shares worth 370.983 million ringgit
(about 104.208 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover rose to 19.331 million shares valued
at 49.724 million ringgit (about 13.967 million U.S. dollars) from
Thursday's 14.287 million shares worth 35.685 million ringgit
(about 10.023 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, off market deals shrank to 4.590 million shares valued
at 23.188 million ringgit (about 6.513 million U.S. dollars) from
8.012 million shares worth 24.421 million ringgit (about 6.859
million U.S. dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 6.608
million shares traded, industrial products 11.299 million,
construction 16.833 million, trade/service 34.938 million,
infrastructure 1.604 million, finance 45.239 million, hotels
719,000, properties 14.000 million, plantations 4.919 million,
mining 2.366 million, trusts 46,000, closed-end fund 118,000 and
loans 26.402 million.  
</P>
