<DOCNO> XIE19980327.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Africa Urged to Promote Stock Mart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The regionalization of stock
markets should become a major step towards sustainable economic
development in Africa, Chairman of the African Stock Exchanges
Association Apostle Alile has said.
</P>
<P>
Promoting regional stock markets is an important part among
African countries' joint efforts to forge stronger common ties
and foster economic integration in the continent, he was quoted
by Friday's Daily Nation newspaper as saying.
</P>
<P>
A regional bourse is helpful where countries encountered
difficulties in accessing external financing while revenue from
taxes remained low, he noted at a one-day seminar held here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The creation of regional stock exchanges was endorsed by the
African Capital Markets Forum and the Inter-governmental Group of
Experts at the Sixth conference of African finance ministers in
Ethiopia last year.
</P>
<P>
The planned east African stock market could promote rapid
growth in cross border trade in bonds and equities, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
"Such an arrangement will provide the respective markets in
the region with liquidity which may not be available at home
while investors will be reducing risks by spreading their
portfolios across national frontiers," said Alile.
</P>
<P>
He added that local companies can gain access to a much larger
pool of external funds by issuing securities in other markets in
east Africa, including Kenya, Uganda and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
"The regional stock market will address the problems of
liquidity, economies of scale and profitability of each stock
market in the sub-region," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, there are problems which would need to be sorted out
before a regional stock exchange can take root, among them the
maintenance of minimum standards for clearing and settlement and
the establishment of a computerized clearing house, he noted.
</P>
<P>
In order for regional stock markets to be promoted, member
countries should harmonize their securities market laws, he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
"Laws must be enacted to prohibit unsafe activities and to
protect investors from a false market. Unfriendly investment laws
such as exchange control measures should be abrogated while sound
economic policies must be adopted," he urged.
</P>
<P>
"Clear disclosure and information requirements and similar
accounting and auditing standards must be established to support
the promotion of a regional financial system," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
