<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Loans Support infrastructure Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- China's State Development Bank
(SDB) provided loans totalling 20.7 billion yuan (2.5 billion US
dollars) during the first quarter of the year to support the
construction of infrastructure, up some 40 percent on last year's
same period.
</P>
<P>
The loans were basically earmarked for the construction of
infrastructure in the sectors of agriculture, forestry, water
conservancy, railway, highway and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The SDB has been conducting appraisals of recipient projects.
</P>
<P>
SDB Governor Yao Zhenyun noted that the eight percent economic
growth rate set by the new National People's Congress and the call
for increased investments in infrastructure are in line with the
bank's service objectives.
</P>
<P>
In addition, priority will be placed on loans to support new
economic growth areas, including the electronics information and
equipment-manufacturing industries, as well as the marine economy,
development of natural resources and key construction projects in
central and western China.
</P>
<P>
Yao said the bank will grant loans to promote the reform of
state-owned enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
