<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Nominates Kiriyenko as Russian PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
said Friday that he has nominated acting Prime Minister Sergei
Kiriyenko as premier, Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, speaking to reporters after meeting with Kiriyenko,
also hoped that the State Duma (the lower house of parliament)
would approve his nomination.
</P>
<P>
Under the Russian constitution, if the State Duma fails to
approve his three nominations, the president has the right to
disband the Duma and call for new parliamentary elections.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko, 35, once Energy Minister, was appointed acting prime
minister after Yeltsin sacked Viktor Chernomyrdin and the whole
government on March 23.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin did it after strongly criticizing the government in
weekend meetings for its chronic failure to pay back wages and
pensions to millions of Russians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
