WASHINGTON -- The United States Senate Thursday approved the
Clinton administration's emergency spending request of 18 billion
U.S. dollars to finance the International Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
The package, approved unanimously by the Senate, also includes
five billion dollars for disaster relief and military deployments
in the Gulf and Bosnia. Earlier in the day, the Senate voted 84 to
16 in support of President Bill Clinton's request for funding the
IMF to deal with the Asian financial crisis. (US-IMF-Approval)
</P>
