</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Serbia hopes with real earnest to cooperate with
the international community on the basis of mutual respect,
equality and the exclusion of pressure, in its efforts to solve
the Kosovo issue, Serbian President Milan Milutinovic said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by the Tanjug news agency as saying that the
international community should not support the Albanian
separatists in Kosovo, but should take a clear position against
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
During separate talks with the United States envoy, Robert
Gelbard, and the European Union representative and British
diplomat, Dzeremi Grinstok, Yugoslavia's Foreign Minister Zironad
Jovanovic reiterated that Kosovo had always been an integral part
of the Republic of Serbia and would remain so in the future.
(Serbia-Kosovo) 
