<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vanessa-Mae to Stage Two Performances in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua)-- Vanessa-Mae, who despite her young
age has been compared with maestros such as Menuhin, Heifetz and
Kreisler, will perform two concerts in Beijing's Capital Stadium
in April.
</P>
<P>
The "true child prodigy like Mozart and Mendelssohn" was the
world's first violinist to record both Tchaikovsky and Beethoven
violin by the age of 13.
</P>
<P>
Vanessa-Mae is not only steeped in the classical discipline ,
but also introduces both acoustic and electric violins in a unique
techo-acoustic fusion considered to be a hybrid of many musical
genres.
</P>
<P>
Some consider her style to be a violation of the classics,
while others applaud her for creating "magic."
</P>
<P>
Vanessa-Mae, 20, completed a violin course at the China Central
conservatory of Music. Her repertoire for the April performances
will include Toccata and Fugue in D Minor, Butterfly Lovers and
Hot Red. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
