<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Film Unveils Assassination Attempt on Mao Zedong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- A film currently being screened
in China portrays an attempted assassination on late Chairman Mao
Zedong during a 1949 visit to the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
Today's Guangming Daily reported that the story is based on an
actual incident. Documents contained in the files of the Ministry
of State Security show that the United States and Kuomintang, led
by Chiang Kai-shek, dispatched special agents to assassinate Mao.
</P>
<P>
The film, jointly produced by the Ministry of Public Security,
Changchun Film Studio and Dalian Dongfang Film and Television
Company, tells how Premier Zhou Enlai and Security Minister Luo
Ruiqing successfully foiled the assassination plot.
</P>
<P>
The arrest of the suspected assassin in Guangzhou, capital of
south China's Guangdong Province, guaranteed Mao's safety.
</P>
<P>
The film premiered in the Great Hall of the People on Thursday,
The producer said the film was made to commemorate the 100th birth
anniversary of Zhou Enlai, founder of China's underground guerilla
network, and the fifth anniversary of adoption of the State
Security Law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
