<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Two Loans and Grant for China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved on
Thursday two loans and a grant totaling 335 million U.S. dollars
for two projects in China.
</P>
<P>
The first loan of 63 million dollars and a grant of 22 million
dollars from the Global Environment Facility (GEF) will be
provided for China's Energy Conservation Project.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to achieve large, sustained and growing
increase in energy efficiency, and associated reduction in
growth of carbon dioxide emissions and other pollutants.
</P>
<P>
Another loan of 250 million dollars is earmarked for China
Jiangsu Power Transmission Project. This project will help
alleviate critical bottlenecks in power transmission
infrastructure and increase electricity trade on a commercial
basis in east China.
</P>
<P>
The goal will be achieved through development of a reliable
500kv high-voltage transmission network, transformation of East
China Electric Power Group Corporation into a modern corporate
entity and implementation of a regional power market for power
exchange and trade. 
