<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Speeds Up Support for South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Thursday a 2 billion U.S. dollar loan to support South Korea's
structural adjustment.
</P>
<P>
The resources will be utilized to enhance financial sector
stability, improving efficiency and competitiveness, strengthening
social safety nets and laying the basis for Korea's return to
strong and sustained growth.
</P>
<P>
The loan is designed to complement the 3 billion dollar
Economic Reconstruction Loan approved by the World Bank late last
year which focused on financial sector restructuring.
</P>
<P>
The reform agenda for the financial sector stresses the need to
deal with troubled financial institution. Also on the agenda are
measures to strengthen the sector's regulatory and institutional
framework.
</P>
<P>
The reform program sets out to strengthen market infrastructure
and the regulatory framework for equity and bond markets to
promote the development of capital markets and encourage the
development of institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
This loan is a single-tranche, fast-disbursing operation with a
maturity of 15 years, including 5 years of grace. It is expected
to be followed by further structural adjustment loans linked to
this country's progress in implementing these reforms and
undertaking additional reforms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
