<HEADLINE> Austria, Lebanon Call for Implementation of U.N. Resolutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Austria and Lebanon on Thursday
called for the unconditional implementation of all the United
Nations resolutions on the Middle East to promote the peace
process in the region and to relieve tensions in the border areas
between Israel and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Austrian Federal Chancellor Viktor Klima and visiting Lebanese
Prime Minister Rafik Hariri made the appeal in a joint statement
issued after their talks.
</P>
<P>
Klima told reporters that the talks between Israel and Syria
should be resumed to practice the formula of "land for peace."
</P>
<P>
Talking about EU's mediation in the Middle East, Klima, whose
country will take over the rotating EU chairmanship in July,
pointed out that the EU will supplement not compete with the
U.S. in its role in the region.
</P>
<P>
Hariri, who arrived here Wednesday on a two-day official visit,
said that Lebanon hopes to live in peace because only peace can
ensure security.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the EU should play a greater role in the
Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Hariri, the first Lebanese prime minister to visit this
country, is also scheduled to meet other Austrian leaders and
entrepreneurs to seek their support in the reconstruction of
Lebanon. 
</P>
