<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Reverses Downturn Trend In Foreign Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province in south
China used 1.75 billion US dollars worth of overseas funds in
the first two months of the year, a year-on-year rise of 24.9
percent and a sure sign that China's foreign investment
readjustments have begun to work.
</P>
<P>
During that period, the number of new overseas investment
contracts was up 1.67 percent and the amount of contractual
overseas capital up 18.3 percent, reversing the downhill slide in
foreign trade and economic cooperation of the past year, local
sources say.
</P>
<P>
The province handled 18.2 billion US dollars worth of imports
and exports in the two-month period, up 19.3 percent, with 11
billion US dollars of that caming from exports, a 22.5 percent
increase.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong plays an important role in China's foreign trade and
economic cooperation. Last year, it used 14.2 billion US dollars
worth of overseas funds and did slightly over 130 billion US
dollars worth of foreign trade, accounting for 22 percent and 40
percent of the national totals, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
