<HEADLINE> Serbia Seeks Cooperation, Respect on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Serbia hopes with real earnesty
to cooperate with the international community on the basis of
mutual respect, equality and the exclusion of pressure, in its
efforts to solve the Kosovo issue, Serbian President Milan
Milutinovic said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by the Tanjug news agency as saying that the
international community should not support the Albanian
separatists in Kosovo, but should take a clear position against
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Milutinovic was meeting the United States envoy, Robert
Gelbard, and the European Union representative and British
diplomat, Dzeremi Grinstok.
</P>
<P>
During separate talks with the two visitors, Yugoslav Foreign
Minister Zironad Jovanovic reiterated that Kosovo had always been
an integral part of the Republic of Serbia and would remain so in
the future.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Kosovo issue must be solved through
dialogue within his republic.
</P>
<P>
Gelbard and Grinstok told the press that the six-nation Contact
Group on the Former Yugoslavia had expressed deep concern about
the failure of the Serbian and Albanian political leaders to
conduct any substantive dialogue on the Kosovo issue so far.
</P>
<P>
If no progress was to be made within four weeks, they warned,
the contact group would need to consider taking other measures on
the issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
