<HEADLINE> Brazilian Pork Export Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The export of Brazilian
pork grew 35 percent in volume and 38.53 percent in value in the
first two months of this year, compared with the same period in
1996.
</P>
<P>
Exports rose from 8,663 tons to 12,000 tons in the same
period, the Pork Exporters Brazilian Association said.
</P>
<P>
The value of the exports went from 17.1 million U.S. dollars to
23.69 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Chicken Exporters Brazilian Association said the
export of its product in January-February was more than 97,000
tons, 10,700 tons less than that in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is an important exporter of pork, beef and chicken. The
exports of meats earned 900 million dollars for the country last
year. 
</P>
