<HEADLINE> Boogerd Retains Lead in Catalan Week Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Dutch rider Jeroen Blijlevens
claimed the victory in the final sprint on Thursday to win the 204
kilometer fourth stage of the Catalan Week cycling race in a time
of five hours, 13 minutes and 35 seconds.
</P>
<P>
But fellow Dutchman Michael Boogerd retained the overall lead
in the race, establishing a 11-second advantage over France's
second-placed Laurent Jalabert.
</P>
<P>
The leading pack was still closely grouped as it entered the
closing sprint around 3.5 kms from the line, and it was not until
the final 50 meters that Blijlevens made his dash for the finish
line.
</P>
<P>
The Italians put in a strong performance with Mario Cipollini
and Nicolas Minali crossing the line second and third
respectively, to end with the same time as Blijlevens. Biagio
Conte finished in fourth position, also with the same time.
</P>
<P>
Swiss rider Alex Zuelle remained in sixth position in the
overall standings, still lagging the leaders by 30 seconds. But
with his preferred time-trial stage ahead of him, he was felt to
still have a realistic chance.
</P>
<P>
Friday's two-leg time-trial leg is a shorter 68kms between
Hospitalet de Llobregat and Sardanyola. 
</P>
