<HEADLINE> Australian Women Advance to Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Australian world champion Sarah
Fitz-Gerald and teammate Michelle Martin advanced to the final of
the women's squash tour Grand Prix finals in Hurghada, Egypt on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Fitz-Gerald defeated British champion Sue Wright 9-0, 9-7, 9-6
in 36 minutes after losing her concentration sufficiently in the
second game to allow the third seeded Wright a 7-3 lead in the
second game and a 5-3 lead in the third.
</P>
<P>
Martin, looking completely concentrated in what she insists is
only a build-up tournament for her defence of the British Open
championship next week in Birmingham, England, dismissed Liz
Irving, another Australian, 9-4, 9-5, 9-1 in just 27 minutes.
</P>
