<HEADLINE> More U.S. Aid to Help Bosnian Serbs Repair Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The United States will provide
an extra three million U.S. dollars in donation to help the Serb
Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina repair its infrastructure,
according to a memorandum of understanding signed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
President of the Serb republic Biljana Plavsic and U.S.
Ambassador to Bosnia Richard Kauzlarich signed the memorandum in
the northwestern city of Banja Luka in Bosnia, the Tanjug News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The aid will be used to repair infrastructure in the western
areas of the Serb republic, the reported said.
</P>
<P>
Twenty three public projects have been repaired or set up with
a previous multi-million-U.S.-dollar aid package.
</P>
<P>
Plavsic expressed her satisfaction at this and urged the
U.S. to provide similar assistance for the eastern areas of the
Serb republic. 
</P>
