<DOCNO> XIE19980327.0234 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Sees High Mortality, Low Birth Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria is currently experiencing
a high adult and infant mortality rate, alongside a low birth rate
and a short life expectancy, statistics released Thursday at a
meeting of the National Development Council stated.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Bulgaria's infant mortality rate reached 15.6 per
1,000, which is much higher than many European countries. The
country's death rate was 14 per 1,000, and its birth rate reached
6 per 1,000, council statistics claim.
</P>
<P>
Life expectancy of people in the country is too short by
European standards, the council said. The average length of life
is 67.1 years for men, and 74.6 years for women. Maternal
mortality is quadruple the average European level.
</P>
<P>
Experts said efforts should be concentrated on reducing the
high death rate. A healthy way of living and raising children's
health awareness are also essential, they added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
