<HEADLINE> Chile's Exports to Asia Decrease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Chile's exports to Asia in the
first two months of this year shrank 23.1 percent to 703.3 million
U.S. dollars, while Chilean imports grew 43.2 percent to 574.6
million dollars, a report from the Central Bank said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the export decrease and import increase
to the financial crisis in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Japan is Chile's leading trade partner in Asia. Japan's
imports, which account for more than 50 percent of Chile's
exports, amounted to 403 million dollars during January-February,
down 10.3 percent from the 449.6 million dollars in the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Chile's exports to China grew 12 percent during the first two
month this year. 
</P>
