<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, March 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Indications show that the Clinton administration
is making some small gestures toward Iran and has eased off its
customary anti-Tehran rhetoric as part of an effort to improve
relations.
</P>
<P>
State Department spokesman James Rubin confirmed Thursday at a
regular briefing that the administration had given permission to
Mohammad Hadi Nejad-Hosseinian, Iran's top diplomat at the United
Nations, to travel to Los Angeles and deliver a speech on April 2
at an Iran-U.S. symposium sponsored by the World Affairs Council.
</P>
<P>
"We have given permission for the Iranian U.N. permanent
representative to travel outside New York City to deliver a speech
to a private American group in Los Angeles," he said.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts said such an overture was quite rare as Iranian
officials at the United Nations could only travel within a limited
area of New York City. (US-Iran)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States said Thursday that it hopes the
arms embargo the United Nations will impose on Yugoslavia next
week will be open-ended.
</P>
<P>
The six-nation Contact Group on the former Yugoslavia met
Wednesday in Bonn and agreed to the embargo on Belgrade unless it
restores autonomy to ethnic Albanians in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"There was some suggestion that perhaps this arms embargo
should be of a limited timeframe," James P. Rubin, the State
Department spokesman, said Thursday. (US-UN-Yugoslavia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin said Thursday he
believed that the Russian-French-German Summit held in Bor resort
near Moscow marks the beginning of the formation of a real
multipolar world, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said this at a press conference after his meeting with
French President Jacques Chirac and German Chancellor Helmut
Kohl. He said, "It is from here that a multipolar world will
evolve, not from any one state, but from a number of states, a
number of leaders."
</P>
<P>
"It is here that a multipolar approach is being formed, and it
is from here that it will spread around the world," he said,
adding there should be no discrimination against any state in the
modern world. (Russia-Summit) 
</P>
