<HEADLINE> Hingis Ousted by Williams at Lipton Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 26 (Xinhua) -- World No. one Martina Hingis
of Switzerland was ousted today by 11th-seeded Venus Williams of
the United States at the semifinals of the Lipton Championships
held at Key Biscayne, Florida.
</P>
<P>
Williams defeated Hingis by 6-2, 5-7, 6-2 to reach the
championship match of the 4.6 million U.S. dollars tournament.
</P>
<P>
The American tennager will meet the winner of the other
semifinal between eighth-seeded Aranxta Sanchez Vicario of Spain
and Anna Kournikova of Russia to be played in Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
In today's match, Venus won the first set in a windy afternoon
and had a 5-3 lead in the second. But Hingis survived three match
points and a mediocre backhand to force a decision third set, in
which she was overpowered.
</P>
<P>
Hingis barely beat Serena Williams, Venus' younger sister, in
Wednesday's quarter-finals. She also defeated Venus Williams last
week in a semifinals at Indian Wells, California.
</P>
<P>
Hingis lost outdoors in the United States for just the second
time in 45 matches over the last two years. She fell to 19-3 this
season, with two of those losses to Venus Williams.  
</P>
</TEXT>
