<HEADLINE> HK Instant-Dict Soccer Team to Play Ajax Amsterdam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's top First Division
soccer team Instant-Dict will play European giants Ajax Amsterdam
from the Netherlands, official of the local club announced here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Ajax is world famous and is one of the top clubs in Europe,"
said Ken Ng, Executive Director of Instant-Dict, "It is runaway
leader in the Dutch league and it will come to Hong Kong to
entertain and to educate the local fans."
</P>
<P>
"At a time when Hong Kong football is going through a new era,
Ajax is the perfect team to demonstrate teamwork, systems and
success," he added.
</P>
<P>
Ajax, current first division leaders and twelve points ahead of
their nearest rivals in domestic league, will make their debut in
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region in the Hong Kong
Stadium on May 24.
</P>
<P>
In the Hong Kong game, Ajax will showcase eight internationals
from their first team squad. A number of other international
players will be on World Cup duty but the strength of the club's
unique rotating system means that their presence will not be
missed.
</P>
<P>
Eight of the members of the coming Dutch side played in the
team's recent European Cup match against Spartak Moscow and nine
played in the team's league match last weekend.  
</P>
</TEXT>
