<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks End Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 26 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks ended lower Thursday
with the Dow Jones industrial average down 25.91 to close at
8,846.89.
</P>
<P>
It opened in a slump mode down nearly 52 points in the morning
after a government report indicating that corporate profits fell
in the fourth quarter of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip index soared to 8,892.98 in the afternoon but
could not extend the trend, instead it dived heavily at the close.
</P>
<P>
Some dealers expect window dressing over the next three trading
sessions till quarter-end to help the Dow touch 9,000. The Dow
first crossed over 8,900 last Friday.
</P>
<P>
On the New York Stock Exchange declining shares led advancers
1,488 up, 1,503 down and 513 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Trading volume amounted to 598.41 million shares against 663.13
million previously.
</P>
<P>
Broader market indicators ended mixed with the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 stock list down 1.13 to 1,100.81 and the NYSE composite
index down 0.55 to 572.21.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index was up 4.03 to
1854.54 and the American Stock Exchange index up 2.50 to 739.39.
</P>
</TEXT>
