<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Donors To Replenish 2.75 Bln Dlrs for Global </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-six donors from both
developing and developing countries have agreed to a second
replenishment of 2.75 billion U.S. dollars for the Global
Environment Facility (GEF), the GEF announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The replenishment comes as the GEF prepares to hold its first
assembly of 162 participating nations in New Delhi in early April.
</P>
<P>
The GEF is a multilateral financing mechanism established in
1991 to provide grant and concessional funds to developing
countries to conserve and use biodiversity sustainably, reduce the
risk of climate change, protect international waters, phase out
ozone depleting substances and combat deforestation and
desertification.
</P>
<P>
The first GEF replenishment took place in 1994. During the
four-year period, some 2 billion dollars were provided. Since
1991, the GEF has allocated 1.9 billion dollars in grant funding
to over 500 projects in 119 countries, leveraging an additional 5
billion dollars in co-financing. GEF projects are implemented by
the United Nations Development Program, the United Nations
Environment Program and the World Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
