<HEADLINE> IDB Supports Judicial Improvements in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) announced here Thursday the approval of a 18.9 million
dollar loan to improve the quality of judicial services in Panama
and to strengthen the rule of law.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used to help finance a program designed to
shorten response time of the legal system, guarantee due process
of law, and lower barriers to citizens access.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the IDB loan, local counterpart funds total 8.1
million dollars for the program.
</P>
<P>
The IDB has been active in recent years in supporting reform of
the state in Panama, including financing by the Multilateral
Investment Fund to carry out a project with the private sector for
commercial arbitration and mediation, as well as financing for
modernization of the legislative branch and fiscal management.
</P>
</TEXT>
